-- Time Warner raises stake in Eidos to about 20 percent
-- 
-- Mon Dec 15, 2008 5:27am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/12/15/us-eidos-timewarner-idUSTRE4BE23O20081215

 

 (Reuters) - Entertainment software developer Eidos Plc said on Monday Time Warner Entertainment, a unit of U.S. media firm Time Warner Inc, bought 10 million shares in Eidos, increasing its stake to 19.92 percent in the company. 

 Eidos, formerly known as SCi Entertainment Group Plc, said Time Warner Entertainment had bought these shares on December 11 and now holds about 52.5 million shares in the company. Eidos, the holding company of Eidos Interactive, has developed interactive video and computer games series such as "Tomb Raider" and "Hitman." At 1022 GMT (5:22 a.m. EST), Eidos shares were up 3 percent at 18 pence. (Reporting by Usman Merchant in Bangalore; Editing by Gopakumar Warrier)